    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0001-3516-5871"
abstract: >-
  Synthesis preprint formulating a conjectural cardinality envelope for the underlying
  group at section level of the fundamental group of the condensed classifying anima of
  a spectral infinity-topos: |pi_1| <= 2^kappa, where kappa is a size invariant of the
  topos defined in the paper. Tested against two direct geometric attestations from
  Haine-Holzschuh-Lara-Mair-Martini-Wolf (2025) and discussed alongside related cardinal
  phenomena in model theory (Lascar groups) and set theory (Whitehead in condensed Ab).
  Falsifiable conjecture with explicit confidence levels per claim and an honest
  declaration of author position and LLM-assisted production method. v1.1 incorporates
  substantive corrections from two anonymous AI reviewers.
keywords:
